A ------------------------------------------> B

i) Either he follows the traffic rules
    He will reach the destination on time.

ii) Either he is not following the traffic rules

    a) He might get into some accident
    b) He might be caught by traffic cop
    c) He might be fined
    d) He might be jailed
    e) He might be caught, fines and Jailed
    f) He might reach his destination late
    h) He might reach his destination without any of the above things happening


    OOPs Concepts:

    -> your code will be safe and secure
    -> Reusable [less lines of code]
    -> we can make use of variables and methods with same name but different outputs
    -> Easy code management


    ENCAPSULATION
       -DATA HIDING

    POLYMORPHISM: Methods with same name but different actions
       -METHOD OVERLOADING: methods with same name & different signature [compile time polymorphism/static polymorphism]
       -METHOD OVERRIDING

    INHERITANCE
        -ABSTRACTION
        -INTERFACE

